:"FIRST","meanings":["Greek: the Lord gave graciously; whom Jehovah gave; whom Jehovah bestowed."],"variants":[]},{"name":"Robert","type":"FIRST","attribution":"Dictionary of First Names © Patrick Hanks and Flavia Hodges 1990, 2003, 2006.","meanings":["One of the many French names of Germanic origin that were introduced into Britain by the Normans; it has since remained in continuous use. It is derived from the nearly synonymous elements <i>hrōd</i> ‘fame’ + <i>berht</i> ‘bright, famous’, and had a native Old English predecessor of similar form (<i>Hreodbeorht</i>), which was supplanted by the Norman name. Two dukes of Normandy in the 11th century bore the name: the father of  William the Conqueror  (sometimes identified with the legendary Robert the Devil), and his eldest son. It was borne also by three kings of Scotland, notably  Robert the Bruce  (  1274–1329 ), who freed Scotland from English domination. The altered short form <i>Bob</i> is very common, but <i>Hob</i> and <i>Dob</i>, which were common in the Middle Ages and gave rise to surnames, are extinct.  See also  Rupert ."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705192,"age":8,"year":"1328","julianDay":2206102,"title":"First War of Scottish Independence","description":"The First War of Scottish Independence began after England invaded Scotland in 1296. The Treaty of Edinburgh was signed in 1328 which declared peace between the two kingdoms and brought the war to an end.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705193,"age":17,"year":"1337","toYear":"1453","julianDay":2209390,"title":"The Hundred Years' War","description":"The Hundred Years' War between France and England was largely due to the question of legitimate succession to the French crown.","jurisdictionLevel":2},{"id":1705195,"age":62,"year":"1382","julianDay":2225826,"title":"Wycliffe's Bible","description":"John Wycliffe, English theologian and professor at the University of Oxford, completed a translation of the Bible from the Latin Vulgate into Middle English. This translation is known as Wycliffe's Bible and was completed around 1382.","url":"https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Wycliffe%27s_Bible","urlTitle":"Wikipedia - Wycliffe's Bible","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When John Robert Atwater was born in 1320, in Lenham, Kent, England, his father, Godfrey Atwater, was 20 and his mother, Mrs. Godfrey Atwater, was 19. He had at least 1 son with Mrs. John Atwater. He died in 1390, in his hometown, at the age of 70."},"et":{"1320–1390":"1320–1390","1322–Female":"1322–Surnud","1345–1395":"1345–1395","1300–1375":"1300–1375","1302–Female":"1302–Surnud","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1322":"1322","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","Lenham, Kent, England":"Lenham, Kent, England"},"fi":{"1320–1390":"1320–1390","1322–Female":"1322–Kuollut","1345–1395":"1345–1395","1300–1375":"1300–1375","1302–Female":"1302–Kuollut","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1322":"1322","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","Lenham, Kent, England":"Lenham, Kent, England"},"fr":{"1320–1390":"1320–1390","1322–Female":"1322–Décédée","1345–1395":"1345–1395","1300–1375":"1300–1375","1302–Female":"1302–Décédée","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","1345":"1345","1300":"1300","1322":"1322","1453":"1453","1320":"1320","1375":"1375","1395":"1395","1382":"1382","1390":"1390","1328":"1328","Lenham, Kent, England":"Lenham, Kent, Angleterre","lifeSummary":"Lorsque John Robert Atwater est né en 1320, à Lenham, Kent, Angleterre, son père, Godfrey Atwater, avait 20 ans et sa mère, Mrs. Godfrey Atwater, avait 19 ans. Il a eu au moins 1 fils avec Mrs. John Atwater. Il est décédé en 1390, dans sa ville natale, à l’âge de 70 ans."},"de":{"1320–1390":"1320–1390","1322–Female":"1322–Verstorben","1345–1395":"1345–1395","1300–1375":"1300–1375","1302–Female":"1302–Verstorben","1337":"1337","1302":"1302","134